summary:
I Graduated cum laude from the Catholic University of Leuven with a master’s degree in biomedical sciences. During my studies, I did a couple of internships in different labs with a wide range of research subjects. One of the internships I did was abroad in Slovenia, where I not only strengthened my research and analytical skills. But I also gained valuable experience in an international setting. My years at the Catholic University of Leuven have greatly improved my analytical skills and advanced my organizational skills.

I’m reliable, flexible, and driven. And as someone who graduated amid a global pandemic, I think I can honestly call myself persistent and say that I can handle stress well.  I have basic knowledge of ICH-GCP guidelines and am familiar with medical terminology.

I’m looking to start an exciting career in the discovery and development of new drugs and therapies and I believe I would be a great asset to your company.
